   New York State Dormitory Authority -- $208 million of City
University of New York consolidated second general resolution
refunding revenue bonds, Series 1990D and 1990E, priced by a
Morgan Stanley &amp; Co. group. The $142.7 million Series 1990D
comprises current interest serial bonds priced to yield from
6.75% in 1998 to 7.40% in 2003 and $95.8 million of 7% term
bonds priced at 94.98 to yield 7.50% in 2009. The $65.3
million Series 1990E comprises current interest serial bonds
priced to yield from 6.75% in 1998 to 7.35% in 2002 and $11
million of 7.75% term bonds priced at par due in 2017. The
bonds are rated single-A/triple-B-plus, except for Series
1990D bonds due in 1998-2000, 2002 and 2003 and Series 1990E
bonds due in 1998-2000 and 2002, which are insured and
triple-A-rated.
   Los Angeles -- $201.3 million of certificates of
participation, Series 1990, priced by a PaineWebber Inc.
group. The cerfificates, for the city's Convention and
Exhibition Center, were priced to yield from 6.20% in 1994 to
7.23% in 2021. Zero-coupon capital appreciation bonds are due
in 2001-2005 and yield from 6.80% to 7.00%. There are $33.1
million of 7% term bonds priced at 98.25 to yield 7.17% in
2010 and $52.7 million of 7% term bonds priced at 97.25 to
yield 7.23% in 2021. The issue is insured and triple-A-rated.
   Philadelphia School District -- $120 million of 6 1/4%
school district tax and revenue anticipation notes, Series
1990-91, due June 28, 1991, tentatively priced by a Merrill
Lynch Capital Markets group to yield 6% in 1991. The notes
are rated MIG-1/SP-1.
   Vermont -- $100 million of 10 1/2-month, 6 1/4% general
obligation temporary notes due June 28, 1991, priced mostly
by a Merrill Lynch Capital Markets group to yield 5.80%. The
notes are rated MIG-1/SP1-Plus.
                                                                                                       

