<HL>
   Business Brief -- Hicks, Muse &amp; Co.:
   Investment Firm to Buy,
   Combine Neodata and TMI
</HL>
<DATE>
08/08/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4
</SO>
<CO>
   GM GME DNB WNEWS
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Hicks, Muse &amp; Co., a Dallas investment partnership, said
it agreed to buy Neodata Services Group of Louisville, Colo.,
from Dun &amp; Bradstreet Corp. for $85 million. The investment
firm also said it will buy TMI Corp., a Dallas data
management concern, for about $14 million.
   After working capital and expenses, the total deal is
estimated at $104 million. It is expected to be completed
within 30 days.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Hicks Muse said it will combine TMI and Neodata, a
magazine subscription service concern, to form a single media
service company, Neodata Holdings Inc., in Boulder, Colo.
Electronic Data Systems Inc., a unit of General Motors Corp.,
is investing $6 million in preferred stock in the purchase of
the two companies. EDS is also an investor in the Hicks, Muse
Equity Fund, which is providing equity for the deal. EDS will
provide data processing services and equipment to the new
holding company.
   Senior management of Neodata and TMI will remain at the
new company and will participate in the investment. Thomas
Hicks, chairman of Hicks Muse, will be chairman and chief
executive officer of Neodata Holdings Inc.
</TEXT>
